  "text": "LLVM Pass Manager Registration and Execution Chain\n\n## Overview\n\nThe LLVM optimization pass system uses two complementary mechanisms: the legacy pass manager (deprecated) and the new pass manager. Both are rooted in a centralized PassRegistry that tracks all available passes.\n\n## 1. PassManager Template System (New PM)\n\nThe core PassManager template is defined in `llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h` (lines 159-226). This is a template class parameterized by the IR unit it operates on (Module, Function, Loop, etc.). The PassManager template:\n- Stores a vector of passes (line 225) as `std::vector<std::unique_ptr<PassConceptT>> Passes`\n- Implements the `addPass()` method (lines 193-214) which stores passes using type erasure via PassModel\n- Contains a `run()` method that sequentially executes all contained passes\n- Two type aliases provided: `ModulePassManager` (line 238) and `FunctionPassManager` (line 247)\n\n## 2. PassRegistry System (Static Registration)\n\nThe PassRegistry is defined in `llvm/include/llvm/PassRegistry.h` and implemented in `llvm/lib/IR/PassRegistry.cpp`. This is a singleton that maintains two maps:\n- `PassInfoMap`: Maps pass type identifiers (&PassClass::ID) to PassInfo objects\n- `PassInfoStringMap`: Maps command-line argument strings to PassInfo objects\n\nThe `registerPass()` method (PassRegistry.cpp:48-62) inserts pass metadata and notifies registration listeners.\n\n## 3. Pass Registration Macros (Legacy PM)\n\nThe legacy pass registration mechanism uses macros defined in `llvm/include/llvm/PassSupport.h`:\n- `INITIALIZE_PASS` (lines 56-58): Expands to create registration code\n- `INITIALIZE_PASS_BEGIN/END` (lines 39-54): Creates a function that constructs PassInfo and calls `registry.registerPass()`\n- These macros generate static initialization functions that execute at program startup\n- `RegisterPass<T>` template (lines 89-98): Allows direct pass registration via global constructor\n\n## 4. PassInfo Metadata\n\nDef